edu.vt.cbil.visda.data
Class DataSetParser

java.lang.Object
  edu.vt.cbil.visda.data.DataSetParser

public class DataSetParser
extends java.lang.Object

A Class to parse and populate DataSet implementors. Data is expected to be simple, tab-delimited data organized into rows and columns with a row of column headers, and a short header preceding all rows with one blank line separating it from the data. For example: 

 # this is a comment
 Name
 Brand
 
 Name   Brand   Sample1 Sample2 Sample3
 jon    Merrel  0       3       4
 joe    Nike    0       4       4
 zzz    NA      3       3       0
The short header allows for any number of comments, and is expected to contain the names of all columns that are NOT part of an experiment.
